  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc1 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1 \u2019\u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Dollars' that perish under vines",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The farmers of Galewela Bambaragaswa Lake area say that the farmers of Galewela Bambaragaswa Lake area are facing a serious threat of destruction of the crops by the time they get dollars from foreign countries after the successful harvest of vine orange cultivation which was introduced to the farmers by the Ministry of Agriculture many years ago to earn dollars in Sri Lanka.",
        "The cultivation of vine oranges has been carried out by a large group of farmers in this area since many years. The growers of Galewela Bambaragaswewa point out that due to the extremely dry weather prevailing these days, kerosene and diesel are not provided to irrigate the vine orange plantations, and the harvest of this plantation is falling under the trees and being destroyed.",
        "The farmers point out that the cultivation of vine oranges is in dire straits due to the lack of proper fertilizers and the lack of various types of insecticides. Due to the non-availability of kerosene required for cultivation from petrol stations, all crops are destroyed and the country receives dollars from foreign countries from this harvest.",
        "These farmers point out that the Department of Agriculture has introduced this economic cultivation by spending a lot of money and in such a case, if at least the responsible authorities of the Agriculture Department or the government intervene to provide the necessary fuel for the fruit cultivation that receives these dollars, not only the farmers but also the country will get dollars.",
        "The businessmen who buy this orange crop, which is in high demand in many foreign countries, say that the demand in foreign countries has increased these days and it is not possible to provide the supply because of the fuel crisis.",
        "It is said that it is not possible to get the harvest due to the rot and destruction of the vine plantation in the Galewela area, where a large harvest was obtained.",
        "The farmers who are engaged in the cultivation of vine oranges said that they have grown not vines, but dollars, that the country receives dollars from their harvest and they use those dollars to bring fuel, but fuel is only given to those who earn rupees, not to themselves, who earn dollars in fuel sales. That it was given.",
        "However, if the government takes a more careful look at the helpless people in the village who earn dollars in this country, hundreds of thousands of farmers will be able to send their crops abroad once again to bring back dollars, otherwise they will be destroyed in this way, they said with great concern. There are"
      ],
